<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>In my git tree I have a commit 3a3fbf96ce at HEAD. From the command line I can create a patch for just that commit as follows:</p> <p><code>$ git format-patch &quot;3a3fbf96ce^&quot;</code></p> <p>or even:</p> <p><code>$ git format-patch &quot;HEAD^&quot;</code></p> <p>I can&#39;t for the life of me figure out how to do this in Magit UI.</p> <p>When I Meta-Space on the one commit it gets highlighted, but W c still prompts me for a revision and I don&#39;t know what to type at that point (3a3fbf96ce^ doesn&#39;t work, unlike the command line).</p> <p>Note that W c does a great job creating multiple patches from a selected range of revisions. It is this &quot;single commit&quot; patch workflow that I can&#39;t figure out.</p> <p>I&#39;m running Magit 20220722.345 [&gt;= 3.3.0-git], Git 2.35.1, Emacs 29.0.50, gnu/linux</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/ForkInBrain"> /u/ForkInBrain </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wnxl3v/magit_question_how_to_gitformatpatch/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wnxl3v/magit_question_how_to_gitformatpatch/">[comments]</a></span>